Job Description:
The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Queens has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
The Attending Anesthesiologist will administer anesthetics to render patients insensitive to pain during surgical and other medical procedures. Examine patient to determine degree of surgical risk and type of anesthetic, and sedation to administer, and discusses findings with medical practitioner concerned with the case. Record type and amount of anesthetic and sedation administered and condition of patient before, during and after anesthesia. The Anesthesiologist will also provide consultative, resuscitative and therapeutic services to patients in shock, respiratory insufficiency, acute or chronic pain. The hospital is easily accessible by public transportation and car from all areas of New York City, New Jersey and Long Island.
Candidates must have a MD degree, ACGME approved residency training in Anesthesiology and be board certified by the ABA or in the process of certification with a valid New York State License, DEA and Medicaid number. Qualified candidates should have strong clinical abilities, communication and interpersonal skills. Experience with public health systems are preferred. We also offer a faculty appointment with the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai commensurate with credentials, experience and qualifications.

Physician-OBGYN Reports To: Chief Medical Officer and Chief Operations Officer
Purpose: The Physician is a primary provider of health services and provides primary care under established protocols and the approved Clinical Policies of WWFHC. Specialty Summary. Prescribes prenatal and postnatal care; performs deliveries in maternity cases. Treats diseases and injuries of female reproductive system by surgical and conservative means. Prepares and review case histories and obtains data through interviews. Examines patients and determines x-ray examinations and clinical laboratory tests required. Interprets test results and evaluates examination findings. Prescribes prenatal and postnatal care, including diets and medication. Directs nurses in procedures for preoperative and postoperative care such as administering sedatives, prescribing diets, and preparing operative area of patients. Applies surgical procedures and coordinates gynecological and obstetrical operations with anesthesiologist. Administers and prescribes such conservative measures of treatment as antibiotics, drugs, and compresses. Treats patients suffering from surgical shock, postoperative hemorrhages, and other complications. Manages obstetrical and gynecological services. Formulates plans and procedures for obstetrical and gynecological services. Schedules operation of obstetrical and gynecological services with other medical activities. Instructs interns and student residents in obstetrical and gynecological procedures. Serves as consultant on obstetrics and gynecology.

Why Mayo Clinic
Why Mayo Clinic?
Perhaps you imagine being part of a team where your colleagues inspire you to stretch and grow beyond your boundaries. Position description
The CRNA team at Mayo Clinic Arizona has grown exponentially in recent years and is now an expansive practice of more than 50 practitioners. The large volume of cases, integrated with ongoing research and education, results in a wide-ranging expertise in the anesthetic management of patients. Mayo Clinic uses the Anesthesia Care Team Model where CRNAs work collaboratively with anesthesiologists to provide the best possible care. As a member of the Mayo Clinic team, there is the opportunity to take part in some of the most advanced procedures, including Heart, Lung, Liver, Pancreas and Kidney transplants, Robotic surgeries in GYN, Urology, General, ENT, Orthopedic, Thoracic, and Cardiac. There is also an extensive Spine and Neurosurgery program as well as new hybrid Cardiothoracic, Vascular and Neurosurgery operating rooms. In addition, CRNAs provide anesthesia services for the Surgery Center, Endoscopy Suite and Proton Beam Center, where a specialized team manages pediatric care. Mayo Clinic Arizona doesn’t offer OB, Burn, or Trauma services. Beyond practice, CRNAs participate in leadership development through involvement on committees, team projects, education and research.

In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

You have the opportunity to become the primary doctor while transitioning with experienced best in class doctors. We are looking for Anesthesiologists with previous experience & background with ketamine who can provide in-home IV Ketamine infusions. You will be working with patients who have been diagnosed by a board certified psychiatrist with Treatment Resistant Depression (TRD), PTSD and other treatment resistant psychiatric disorders who may benefit from IV Ketamine infusions.
Patients will always be screened for strict inclusion and exclusion criteria by our psychiatry staff through a virtual appointment. If patients meet our criteria, they will be enrolled into future treatments with IV Ketamine, with you in the comfort of their home. You will be paired with a registered nurse as well to assist you with post IV care monitoring.
This is a great opportunity to make a positive impact on patients with TRD while experiencing an excellent income source and great work-life balance.
Anesthesiologist that successfully complete our interview process, will be matched with one of our partner Professional Corporations to start treating patients. You will be provided with a ketamine infusion step by step protocol and training session. We work currently in New York and California and will be opening service in all major cities over the next year. Your placement will be made with your clinical preferences, state license, experience and schedule in mind.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Queens has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
The Attending Anesthesiologist will administer anesthetics to render patients insensitive to pain during surgical and other medical procedures. Examine patient to determine degree of surgical risk and type of anesthetic, and sedation to administer, and discusses findings with medical practitioner concerned with the case. Record type and amount of anesthetic and sedation administered and condition of patient before, during and after anesthesia. The Anesthesiologist will also provide consultative, resuscitative and therapeutic services to patients in shock, respiratory insufficiency, acute or chronic pain. The hospital is easily accessible by public transportation and car from all areas of New York City, New Jersey and Long Island.
Candidates must have a MD degree, ACGME approved residency training in Anesthesiology and be board certified by the ABA or in the process of certification with a valid New York State License, DEA and Medicaid number. Qualified candidates should have strong clinical abilities, communication and interpersonal skills. Experience with public health systems are preferred. We also offer a faculty appointment with the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai commensurate with credentials, experience and qualifications.

Contract with AMCE Physicians Group performing evaluations for the Social Security Disability Office as an Independent contractor. This would prove to be an excellent opportunity for you to earn extra income on your days off.
The compensation is on a per evaluation basis. Each evaluation for disability is an objective history and exam including a brief record review and dictation
The work is risk-free because you examine each individual one time. There is no overhead, testing, or follow-up. You would not be asked to make the decision as to whether the claimant is disabled. The decision is made by the individual’s caseworker at the Social Security Disability Office. There is no overhead because you perform all exams in our clinics. Support staff is provided, the dictation line is toll-free and our transcription department will transcribe your dictated reports. We handle all administrative issues, as well as the professional liability insurance coverage.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Queens has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
The Attending Anesthesiologist will administer anesthetics to render patients insensitive to pain during surgical and other medical procedures. Examine patient to determine degree of surgical risk and type of anesthetic, and sedation to administer, and discusses findings with medical practitioner concerned with the case. Record type and amount of anesthetic and sedation administered and condition of patient before, during and after anesthesia. The Anesthesiologist will also provide consultative, resuscitative and therapeutic services to patients in shock, respiratory insufficiency, acute or chronic pain. The hospital is easily accessible by public transportation and car from all areas of New York City, New Jersey and Long Island.
Candidates must have a MD degree, ACGME approved residency training in Anesthesiology and be board certified by the ABA or in the process of certification with a valid New York State License, DEA and Medicaid number. Qualified candidates should have strong clinical abilities, communication and interpersonal skills. Experience with public health systems are preferred. We also offer a faculty appointment with the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai commensurate with credentials, experience and qualifications.

Contract with AMCE Physicians Group performing evaluations for the Social Security Disability Office as an Independent contractor. This would prove to be an excellent opportunity for you to earn extra income on your days off.
The compensation is on a per evaluation basis. Each evaluation for disability is an objective history and exam including a brief record review and dictation
The work is risk-free because you examine each individual one time. There is no overhead, testing, or follow-up. You would not be asked to make the decision as to whether the claimant is disabled. The decision is made by the individual’s caseworker at the Social Security Disability Office. There is no overhead because you perform all exams in our clinics. Support staff is provided, the dictation line is toll-free and our transcription department will transcribe your dictated reports. We handle all administrative issues, as well as the professional liability insurance coverage.

Contract with AMCE Physicians Group performing evaluations for the Social Security Disability Office as an Independent contractor. This would prove to be an excellent opportunity for you to earn extra income on your days off.
The compensation is on a per evaluation basis. Each evaluation for disability is an objective history and exam including a brief record review and dictation
The work is risk-free because you examine each individual one time. There is no overhead, testing, or follow-up. You would not be asked to make the decision as to whether the claimant is disabled. The decision is made by the individual’s caseworker at the Social Security Disability Office. There is no overhead because you perform all exams in our clinics. We handle all administrative issues, as well as the professional liability insurance coverage.

Job Description:

CompHealth is assisting a single-specialty group in Ohio with their search for a pediatric anesthesiologist. They are opening 2 new ambulatory surgical centers that will be doing bariatric, ophthalmology, ENT, and plastic cases. Procedures will include 40% pediatric, ENT, tonsils, adenoids, tubes in ear, squints, low level/minimally invasive spine, plastics, and orthopedics. The incoming physician will run 1 to 2 rooms at a time. If it is 1 room, it will be 100% their own cases in that room. If there are 2 rooms, it will be a mix of supervision and doing their own cases. The typical workday will be from 8 am to 4 pm with every other Friday off for a good work-life balance. There will also be no call, weekend, or holiday coverage. Candidates must be in process or already licensed in Ohio to be considered.
This is a 1099 position where you will be responsible for your health, dental, and vision insurance. You will handle your own malpractice options individually or with the group and have the premium deducted from your compensation. A pension plan is in place with a deduction from your compensation as well.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Queens has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
The Attending Anesthesiologist will administer anesthetics to render patients insensitive to pain during surgical and other medical procedures. Examine patient to determine degree of surgical risk and type of anesthetic, and sedation to administer, and discusses findings with medical practitioner concerned with the case. Record type and amount of anesthetic and sedation administered and condition of patient before, during and after anesthesia. The Anesthesiologist will also provide consultative, resuscitative and therapeutic services to patients in shock, respiratory insufficiency, acute or chronic pain. The hospital is easily accessible by public transportation and car from all areas of New York City, New Jersey and Long Island.
Candidates must have a MD degree, ACGME approved residency training in Anesthesiology and be board certified by the ABA or in the process of certification with a valid New York State License, DEA and Medicaid number. Qualified candidates should have strong clinical abilities, communication and interpersonal skills. Experience with public health systems are preferred. We also offer a faculty appointment with the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai commensurate with credentials, experience and qualifications.

Contract with AMCE Physicians Group performing evaluations for the Social Security Disability Office as an Independent contractor. This would prove to be an excellent opportunity for you to earn extra income on your days off.
The compensation is on a per evaluation basis. Each evaluation for disability is an objective history and exam including a brief record review and dictation
The work is risk-free because you examine each individual one time. There is no overhead, testing, or follow-up. You would not be asked to make the decision as to whether the claimant is disabled. The decision is made by the individual’s caseworker at the Social Security Disability Office. There is no overhead because you perform all exams in our clinics. Support staff is provided, the dictation line is toll-free and our transcription department will transcribe your dictated reports. We handle all administrative issues, as well as the professional liability insurance coverage.

Job Title: Medical Doctor / Doctor of Osteopathy for Physicals - Part Time
Job Description:
Currently seeking physicians to perform disability examinations on adults in Evantson, WY. All physical specialties may apply. PAs and NPs may participate in these evaluations as well. Providers must be willing to do full body exams on applicants.
The examinations are not for treatment. We would coordinate scheduling applicants in your office. We provide you with templates to assure report consistency and program adherence.
The examinations are not for the physician to determine whether the applicant is disabled or not. The reports summarized from these encounters will help the decision-makers in determining whether a disability is present under their programmatic guidelines and whether the applicant qualifies for benefits.
We provide the administrative support to schedule, confirm appointments, invoice, bill, rebill and manage medical records for these claims. We provide a dictation and transcription service at no cost. You are assured payment whether our client pays us or not.

The physician will provide comprehensive multi-disciplinary pain management care and may supervise ARNPs/Physician Assistants. Position requires a variety of clinical and technical skills including coordination, workup, diagnosis, treatment, interventional and medical management with follow up of pain patients. Clinic hours are 7:30am-4:30pm Monday – Friday. Position offers a competitive salary guarantee with productivity based incentive from the beginning of employment, along with a comprehensive benefits package including medical, dental, vision and 401k opportunities with company match. Employee shall receive three (3) weeks paid time off and five (5) days of paid CME with reimbursement up to three thousand ($3500.00) dollars per year. There is as immediate partnership track to buy into our ASC offered and details will be discussed upon interview.

The origins of NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst can be traced back to the mid-1800s when it was built as City Hospital to serve the poor. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

Job Description
Partnership, Buy-in or buy-out is now an option but must be prepared to move on the deal or re-locate immediately!
A multi-disciplinary group in beautiful Southwest coastal Florida is looking for a pending board or board certified pain management physician in interventional pain management/anesthesiologists. You can be an experienced physician, new physician or awaiting boards and looking for a new growth opportunity that has the feel of a small team approach in which you will make all of your own clinical decisions. You will join two retiring double board certified interventional pain management anesthesiologists, a physician assistant and the nursing staff. We will soon be adding another PA, NP, physical therapy and other modalities. We want to find a permanent candidate as soon as possible so Florida licensed physicians are preferred. You will perform 100 percent pain management procedures as well as clinicals. No anesthesia here. This facility has state-of-the-art rooms with C-arms, and shortly adding ultrasound guided equipment. Salary will be negotiated with the physician directly. This offer has an ownership/equity component built in so that you can have a piece of the pie. Your work schedule will be Monday through Friday and never on call or weekends. You will never be directed to the dangerous front lines as now seen in the hospital systems or giant furloughs as we are currently seeing. It is an ideal location in an upscale community for every water activity, quick trip to the keys, and is 30 minutes to Fort Myers. You can also enjoy a variety of cultural and recreational events offered throughout the year. For more information, please contact David Ellis at 517-930-7022 Quick Facts: Growing location with the plan to have 10 locations and the individual who comes on board NOW, will have the opportunity to have an equity stake in ALL locations for a win win scenario. This location will be adding many different types of practitioners and implementing the future of pain management with the latest procedures and techniques available along with sound clinical evidence based regenerative medicine. You have the opportunity to become the primary doctor while transitioning with experienced best in class doctors. Fresh new ideas in a small environment without the hassle of running your own practice and without being some puppet in a large group or hospital setting. Come in, see patients, and live life.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Elmhurst has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
Elmhurst Hospital is a Level 1 Adult Trauma Center. In addition, anesthetic care is provided for a robust Obstetrical Service. A Pain management Clinic and Acute Pain Service are also provided. The origins of NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst can be traced back to the mid-1800s when it was built as City Hospital to serve the poor. It was the first hospital in the nation to substantially reduce incidences of puerperal or “childbed” fever among its maternity ward patients. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Elmhurst has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
Elmhurst Hospital is a Level 1 Adult Trauma Center. In addition, anesthetic care is provided for a robust Obstetrical Service. A Pain management Clinic and Acute Pain Service are also provided. The Anesthesia Department provides care for thriving General Surgery and Orthopedics Services. Elmhurst Hospital is a Joint Commission Accredited Center for Knee and Hip Joint Replacement. We provide anesthetic care for a variety of cases excluding cardiac and transplant. We also provide care for low acuity pediatric cases. The anesthesiologist will be involved in direct clinical patient care and may supervise Mount Sinai Anesthesiology residents. The anesthesiologist may also supervise Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetists. The work environment is collegiate and supportive.
The origins of NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst can be traced back to the mid-1800s when it was built as City Hospital to serve the poor. It was the first hospital in the nation to substantially reduce incidences of puerperal or “childbed” fever among its maternity ward patients. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

It was the first hospital in the nation to substantially reduce incidences of puerperal or “childbed” fever among its maternity ward patients. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Elmhurst has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
Elmhurst Hospital is a Level 1 Adult Trauma Center. In addition, anesthetic care is provided for a robust Obstetrical Service. A Pain management Clinic and Acute Pain Service are also provided. The Anesthesia Department provides care for thriving General Surgery and Orthopedics Services. Elmhurst Hospital is a Joint Commission Accredited Center for Knee and Hip Joint Replacement. We provide anesthetic care for a variety of cases excluding cardiac and transplant. We also provide care for low acuity pediatric cases. The anesthesiologist will be involved in direct clinical patient care and may supervise Mount Sinai Anesthesiology residents. The anesthesiologist may also supervise Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetists. The work environment is collegiate and supportive.
The origins of NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst can be traced back to the mid-1800s when it was built as City Hospital to serve the poor. It was the first hospital in the nation to substantially reduce incidences of puerperal or “childbed” fever among its maternity ward patients. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

Contract with AMCE Physicians Group performing evaluations for the Social Security Disability Office as an Independent contractor. This would prove to be an excellent opportunity for you to earn extra income on your days off.
The compensation is on a per evaluation basis. Each evaluation for disability is an objective history and exam including a brief record review and dictation
The work is risk-free because you examine each individual one time. There is no overhead, testing, or follow-up. You would not be asked to make the decision as to whether the claimant is disabled. The decision is made by the individual’s caseworker at the Social Security Disability Office. There is no overhead because you perform all exams in our clinics. Support staff is provided, the dictation line is toll-free and our transcription department will transcribe your dictated reports. We handle all administrative issues, as well as the professional liability insurance coverage.

There is as immediate partnership track to buy into our ASC offered and details will be discussed upon interview.

Strong NP/PA support

This is an excellent opportunity to join a very reputable and established group of highly trained interventional pain physicians and mid-level practitioners. Located an hour from the Triangle area and close to both the beautiful beaches and majestic mountains of North Carolina.

Excellent work life balance with no weekends.

Job Description
Partnership, Buy-in or buy-out is now an option but must be prepared to move on the deal or re-locate immediately!
A multi-disciplinary group in beautiful Southwest coastal Florida is looking for a pending board or board certified pain management physician in interventional pain management/anesthesiologists. You can be an experienced physician, new physician or awaiting boards and looking for a new growth opportunity that has the feel of a small team approach in which you will make all of your own clinical decisions. You will join two retiring double board certified interventional pain management anesthesiologists, a physician assistant and the nursing staff. We will soon be adding another PA, NP, physical therapy and other modalities. We want to find a permanent candidate as soon as possible so Florida licensed physicians are preferred. You will perform 100 percent pain management procedures as well as clinicals. No anesthesia here. This facility has state-of-the-art rooms with C-arms, and shortly adding ultrasound guided equipment. Salary will be negotiated with the physician directly. This offer has an ownership/equity component built in so that you can have a piece of the pie. Your work schedule will be Monday through Friday and never on call or weekends. You will never be directed to the dangerous front lines as now seen in the hospital systems or giant furloughs as we are currently seeing. It is an ideal location in an upscale community for every water activity, quick trip to the keys, and is 30 minutes to Fort Myers. You can also enjoy a variety of cultural and recreational events offered throughout the year. For more information, please contact David Ellis at 517-930-7022 Quick Facts: Growing location with the plan to have 10 locations and the individual who comes on board NOW, will have the opportunity to have an equity stake in ALL locations for a win win scenario. This location will be adding many different types of practitioners and implementing the future of pain management with the latest procedures and techniques available along with sound clinical evidence based regenerative medicine. You have the opportunity to become the primary doctor while transitioning with experienced best in class doctors. Fresh new ideas in a small environment without the hassle of running your own practice and without being some puppet in a large group or hospital setting. Come in, see patients, and live life.

Traveling Anesthesiologist - A Stable Adventure

Applicants Only. No Agencies Please

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with New York City H + H/Elmhurst has an exciting opportunity for an Attending Anesthesiologist.
Elmhurst Hospital is a Level 1 Adult Trauma Center. In addition, anesthetic care is provided for a robust Obstetrical Service. A Pain management Clinic and Acute Pain Service are also provided. The Anesthesia Department provides care for thriving General Surgery and Orthopedics Services. Elmhurst Hospital is a Joint Commission Accredited Center for Knee and Hip Joint Replacement. We provide anesthetic care for a variety of cases excluding cardiac and transplant. We also provide care for low acuity pediatric cases. The anesthesiologist will be involved in direct clinical patient care and may supervise Mount Sinai Anesthesiology residents. The anesthesiologist may also supervise Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetists. The work environment is collegiate and supportive.
The origins of NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst can be traced back to the mid-1800s when it was built as City Hospital to serve the poor. It was the first hospital in the nation to substantially reduce incidences of puerperal or “childbed” fever among its maternity ward patients. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.

Contract with AMCE Physicians Group performing evaluations for the Social Security Disability Office as an Independent contractor. This would prove to be an excellent opportunity for you to earn extra income on your days off.
The compensation is on a per evaluation basis. Each evaluation for disability is an objective history and exam including a brief record review and dictation
The work is risk-free because you examine each individual one time. There is no overhead, testing, or follow-up. You would not be asked to make the decision as to whether the claimant is disabled. The decision is made by the individual’s caseworker at the Social Security Disability Office. There is no overhead because you perform all exams in our clinics. Support staff is provided, the dictation line is toll-free and our transcription department will transcribe your dictated reports. We handle all administrative issues, as well as the professional liability insurance coverage.

The origins of NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst can be traced back to the mid-1800s when it was built as City Hospital to serve the poor. It was the first hospital in the nation to substantially reduce incidences of puerperal or “childbed” fever among its maternity ward patients. The current facility, now re-named NYC Health + Hospitals/Elmhurst and erected by the Department of Public Works, opened in 1957. In 1964, the hospital became affiliated with the Mount Sinai Hospital and Icahn School of Medicine.
